Pre-Game Insights: Cyprus seeks to break their losing streak, while Lithuania aims for an away result.
Lithuania’s struggles away from home and Cyprus’s determination to end on a positive note in this low-stakes encounter.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cyprus and Lithuania will meet in Limassol for a friendly match, concluding their Euro 2024 qualifying campaigns.
Neither side posed a threat to the top two spots in their respective groups.
Cyprus endured a disappointing Euro 2024 qualifying run, suffering an 8th consecutive defeat against Spain with a 3-1 loss.
Lithuania, in contrast, had a better qualifying campaign, securing their position above Bulgaria in their group.
Others: Cyprus manager Ketsbaia might experiment with the lineup but could call upon key players like Grigoris Kastanos.
Lithuania will miss Eligijus Jankauskas and Paulius Golubickas due to injuries, while Artemijus Tutyskinas remains a long-term absentee.
